		               <h1 class="content-body--top-heading popin-wrapper--header">
                                                        
                                                       
                                                           Manage Your Fidelity<sup>®</sup> Visa Signature<sup>®</sup> Card
                                                        

                                           </h1>	
		
		
		<p class="content-body--top-lede">
			Here's your guide to using your Fidelity<sup>®</sup> Visa Signature<sup>®</sup> Card.
		</p>
		
           
	
	</div>
<div class="popin-wrapper--body">
       <div id="BVRRSummaryContainer" class="ratings-reviews-strip"></div>

	<article id="fmr-bodycontent-component" data-fmrtoctcmid="tcm:526-167924" class="content-body--article">
	<section>
			   
						
					   

					   		   
						                             
                                                   		
				                 	
				
						                            

					  
							   <table class="table-simple stackable-540">
<thead>
<tr>
<th width="20%"><strong>I want to...</strong></th>
<th width="45%"><strong>How can I do this?</strong></th>
<th width="35%"><strong>What can I expect?</strong></th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td id="I want to..." style="border-top:1px dotted #DBDBDB">
<p>Find my credit card information</p>
</td>
<td id="How can I do this?">
<p>After logging in to your <a href="https://scs.fidelity.com/customeronly/portfolio.shtml" id="Link_1472743232462" name="Link_1472743232462" class="">Portfolio<span class="off-screen">Log In Required</span></a>, you'll see your credit cards listed:</p>
<ul>
<li>Select your Credit Card</li>
<li>The Manage Money & Payments page opens with your <a href="https://oltx.fidelity.com/ftgw/fbc/ofcashmgmt/cashMgmtApp?ACCOUNT=&ACCOUNTS=&GOTO=CCT" id="Link_1472583895452" name="Link_1472583895452" class="">Credit Card Snapshot<span class="off-screen">Log In Required</span></a></li>
</ul>
<p>To manage your card through Elan Financial Services:</p>
<ul>
<li>Go to <a href="http://www.fidelityrewards.com/login" id="Link_1444079950939" title="Opens in a new window." target="_blank" class="popup" name="Link_1444079950939" onclick="advancedlink('http://www.fidelityrewards.com/login','You are now leaving Fidelity.com for a web site that is unaffiliated with Fidelity. Fidelity has not been involved in the preparation of the content supplied at the unaffiliated site and does not guarantee or assume any responsibility for its content.','', 'Link_1444079950939')">fidelityrewards.com/login<span class="off-screen">Opens in a new window</span></a></li>
<li>On your first visit, you'll set up a new username and password</li>
</ul>
</td>
<td id="What else should I know?">
<p>Your Credit Card Snapshot is where you can:</p>
<ul>
<li>View statements and posted/pending transactions</li>
<li>Make payments and set up automatic payments</li>
<li>Check your balances</li>
<li>Manage and redeem reward points</li>
</ul>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td id="I want to..." style="border-top:1px dotted #DBDBDB">
<p>View my online statements</p>
</td>
<td id="How can I do this?">
<p>From your <a href="https://oltx.fidelity.com/ftgw/fbc/ofcashmgmt/cashMgmtApp?ACCOUNT=&ACCOUNTS=&GOTO=CCT" id="Link_1472583895452" name="Link_1472583895452" class="">Credit Card Snapshot<span class="off-screen">Log In Required</span></a>, select View Statements for a list of your available statements.</p>
</td>
<td id="What else should I know?">
<p>You can view 18 months of statements online.</p>
<p>Note: Statements prior to August 2016 from the previous issuer are available <strong>by mail</strong> only.</p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td id="I want to..." style="border-top:1px dotted #DBDBDB">
<p>Request statement copies</p>
</td>
<td id="How can I do this?">
<p>From your <a href="https://oltx.fidelity.com/ftgw/fbc/ofcashmgmt/cashMgmtApp?ACCOUNT=&ACCOUNTS=&GOTO=CCT" id="Link_1472583895452" name="Link_1472583895452" class="">Credit Card Snapshot<span class="off-screen">Log In Required</span></a>, select Account Services:</p>
<ul>
<li>Enter the beginning and ending dates of the statements you want to receive</li>
<li>Statements prior to August 2016 from the previous issuer are available <strong>by mail</strong> only</li>
<li>You can also call <a href="javascript:void(0);" id="Link_1472584772061" name="Link_1472584772061" onclick="DisplayPopIn('tcm:526-249602', 'Link_1472584772061', '350', 'false')">Elan Cardmember Service</a></li>
</ul>
</td>
<td id="What else should I know?">
<ul>
<li>You should receive your statements within 1–2 weeks</li>
<li>You may be charged a $5 fee for each statement</li>
<li>You can order up to 7 years of statements</li>
</ul>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td id="I want to..." style="border-top:1px dotted #DBDBDB">
<p>View my transactions</p>
</td>
<td id="How can I do this?">
<p>From your <a href="https://oltx.fidelity.com/ftgw/fbc/ofcashmgmt/cashMgmtApp?ACCOUNT=&ACCOUNTS=&GOTO=CCT" id="Link_1472583895452" name="Link_1472583895452" class="">Credit Card Snapshot<span class="off-screen">Log In Required</span></a>, select View Transactions:</p>
<ul>
<li>You'll see the last 6 months of your transactions</li>
<li>You can view Posted and Pending transactions</li>
</ul>
</td>
<td> </td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td id="I want to..." style="border-top:1px dotted #DBDBDB">
<p>Understand my payment options</p>
</td>
<td id="How can I do this?">
<p>There are a few ways to make credit card payments:</p>
<ul>
<li>Use Elan's payment services: AutoPay or Make a Payment, <strong>or</strong></li>
<li>Use <a href="/customer-service/how-to-set-up-and-use-bill-pay" id="Link_1472584831097" name="Link_1472584831097">Fidelity BillPay<sup>®</sup></a>, <strong>or</strong></li>
<li>Set up third-party payments on your bank's or another financial service's website, <strong>or</strong></li>
<li>Call <a href="javascript:void(0);" id="Link_1472584772061" name="Link_1472584772061" onclick="DisplayPopIn('tcm:526-249602', 'Link_1472584772061', '350', 'false')">Elan Cardmember Service</a>, <strong>or</strong></li>
<li>Mail a check to <a href="javascript:void(0);" id="Link_1472584968100" name="Link_1472584968100" onclick="DisplayPopIn('tcm:526-249625', 'Link_1472584968100', '350', 'false')">Elan</a></li>
</ul>
</td>
<td id="What else should I know?">
<p>If you're using Fidelity BillPay<sup>®</sup> or another payment method, rather than Elan's payment services, please make your payment to <strong>Elan Financial Services</strong>.</p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td id="I want to..." style="border-top:1px dotted #DBDBDB">
<p>Set up a payment account</p>
</td>
<td id="How can I do this?">
<p>From your <a href="https://oltx.fidelity.com/ftgw/fbc/ofcashmgmt/cashMgmtApp?ACCOUNT=&ACCOUNTS=&GOTO=CCT" id="Link_1472583895452" name="Link_1472583895452" class="">Credit Card Snapshot<span class="off-screen">Log In Required</span></a>, under Credit Card Management, select Set Up AutoPay:</p>
<ul>
<li>Under Payment tab, select Make a Payment or AutoPay</li>
<li>Follow the steps to add a payment account</li>
</ul>
<p>Note: These steps only set up your payment account; you are not making a payment.</p>
</td>
<td id="What else should I know?">
<p>After you've added the payment account, select the Payment tab to proceed to AutoPay or Make a Payment.</p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td id="I want to..." style="border-top:1px dotted #DBDBDB">
<p>Use Elan's payment services: AutoPay or <a href="javascript:void(0);" id="Link_1472585004070" name="Link_1472585004070" onclick="DisplayPopIn('tcm:526-249603', 'Link_1472585004070', '350', 'false')">Make a Payment</a></p>
</td>
<td id="How can I do this?">
<p>After you've added a payment account, on your <a href="https://oltx.fidelity.com/ftgw/fbc/ofcashmgmt/cashMgmtApp?ACCOUNT=&ACCOUNTS=&GOTO=CCT" id="Link_1472583895452" name="Link_1472583895452" class="">Credit Card Snapshot<span class="off-screen">Log In Required</span></a>, under Credit Card Management:</p>
<ul>
<li>Select AutoPay and the Payment tab displays</li>
<li>Choose AutoPay or Make a Payment</li>
<li>Indicate if you're paying the minimum, the full balance, <strong>or</strong></li>
<li>Select Other Amount and enter the dollar amount</li>
<li>Select a Payment Day</li>
<li>Review the information and Submit</li>
</ul>
</td>
<td id="What else should I know?">
<p>When you enroll in AutoPay, please continue to make regular payments until you see the AutoPay confirmation on your statement.</p>
<ul>
<li>If you set up Payment Posted alerts, you'll get an email or text confirming your payments</li>
<li>You can add another payment account or change the existing account you've set up</li>
</ul>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td id="I want to..." style="border-top:1px dotted #DBDBDB">
<p>Get payment reminders and other account alerts</p>
</td>
<td id="How can I do this?">
<p>From your <a href="https://oltx.fidelity.com/ftgw/fbc/ofcashmgmt/cashMgmtApp?ACCOUNT=&ACCOUNTS=&GOTO=CCT" id="Link_1472583895452" name="Link_1472583895452" class="">Credit Card Snapshot<span class="off-screen">Log In Required</span></a>, under Credit Card Management, select Set up Alerts:</p>
<ul>
<li>Find the alert you want</li>
<li>Activate the alert by selecting Setup (or Edit or Delete)</li>
<li>Select Save</li>
</ul>
</td>
<td id="What else should I know?">
<ul>
<li>Alerts are sent to the email address or phone number you've provided</li>
<li>Each alert must be set up, edited, or deleted separately</li>
<li>Account alerts track transactions in real time and are <strong>not</strong> the same as fraud notifications</li>
</ul>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td id="I want to..." style="border-top:1px dotted #DBDBDB">
<p>Report unauthorized transactions or a lost or stolen card</p>
</td>
<td id="How can I do this?">
<p>Please call <a href="javascript:void(0);" id="Link_1472584772061" name="Link_1472584772061" onclick="DisplayPopIn('tcm:526-249602', 'Link_1472584772061', '350', 'false')">Elan Cardmember Service</a>.</p>
</td>
<td id="What else should I know?">
<ul>
<li>Set up fraud notifications to monitor suspicious activity</li>
<li>You're not responsible for charges you didn't make or authorize<sup>1</sup></li>
</ul>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td id="I want to..." style="border-top:1px dotted #DBDBDB">
<p>Set up fraud notifications for suspicious activity</p>
</td>
<td id="How can I do this?">
<p>From your <a href="https://oltx.fidelity.com/ftgw/fbc/ofcashmgmt/cashMgmtApp?ACCOUNT=&ACCOUNTS=&GOTO=CCT" id="Link_1472583895452" name="Link_1472583895452" class="">Credit Card Snapshot<span class="off-screen">Log In Required</span></a>, select Account Services and then Profile:</p>
<ul>
<li>Choose Update Contact Info</li>
<li>On the Update Contact Information page, scroll to the phone number section</li>
<li>Enter your text-enabled cell phone number to confirm you'd like to receive fraud notifications</li>
</ul>
</td>
<td id="What else should I know?">
<p>You'll receive text messages or phone calls to alert you to any suspicious account activity.</p>
<p>Note: Fraud notifications are <strong>not</strong> the same as account alerts, but they can be used together to track your card's activity.</p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td id="I want to..." style="border-top:1px dotted #DBDBDB">
<p>Set up or manage travel notifications</p>
</td>
<td id="How can I do this?">
<p>From your <a href="https://oltx.fidelity.com/ftgw/fbc/ofcashmgmt/cashMgmtApp?ACCOUNT=&ACCOUNTS=&GOTO=CCT" id="Link_1472583895452" name="Link_1472583895452" class="">Credit Card Snapshot<span class="off-screen">Log In Required</span></a>, select Account Services and then select Travel Notification:</p>
<ul>
<li>Enter your trip dates and the state or country you'll visit</li>
<li>Your list of upcoming trips displays on the page</li>
</ul>
</td>
<td id="What else should I know?">
<ul>
<li>You can also add another destination or trip</li>
<li>If your plans change, you can delete travel notifications</li>
</ul>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td id="I want to..." style="border-top:1px dotted #DBDBDB">
<p>Add an authorized user on my card</p>
</td>
<td id="How can I do this?">
<p>From your <a href="https://oltx.fidelity.com/ftgw/fbc/ofcashmgmt/cashMgmtApp?ACCOUNT=&ACCOUNTS=&GOTO=CCT" id="Link_1472583895452" name="Link_1472583895452" class="">Credit Card Snapshot<span class="off-screen">Log In Required</span></a>, select Account Services and then select Add an Authorized User:</p>
<ul>
<li>Add the authorized user information, <strong>or</strong></li>
<li>Call <a href="javascript:void(0);" id="Link_1472584772061" name="Link_1472584772061" onclick="DisplayPopIn('tcm:526-249602', 'Link_1472584772061', '350', 'false')">Elan Cardmember Service</a></li>
</ul>
</td>
<td id="What else should I know?">
<ul>
<li>You should receive the card for the new authorized user within 10 days</li>
<li>Elan sends the authorized user's card to the primary account holder's address</li>
</ul>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td id="I want to..." style="border-top:1px dotted #DBDBDB">
<p>Apply for a new card</p>
</td>
<td id="How can I do this?">
<p>You can apply online for the <a href="/cash-management/visa-signature-card" id="Link_1472585732972" name="Link_1472585732972">Fidelity<sup>®</sup> Rewards Visa Signature<sup>®</sup> Card</a> or the <a href="/529-plans/529-visa-signature-credit-card" id="Link_1472585741841" name="Link_1472585741841">Fidelity Investments 529 College Rewards<sup>®</sup> Visa Signature<sup>®</sup> Card</a>.</p>
</td>
<td id="What else should I know?">
<ul>
<li>Take advantage of 2% cash back awards<sup>2</sup></li>
<li>Make purchases using your mobile device</li>
<li>Link your card to any eligible Fidelity accounts</li>
</ul>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
					  
					  
		  
	</section>

                                      <h3 class="expand-collapse--title"></h3>
<ul class="expand-collapse--list">
	 
		
		<li class="expand-collapse--question">
			<a href="#" class="expand-collapse--head expand-collapse--fancyexpand">How do I make mobile payments with my Fidelity<sup>®</sup> Visa Signature<sup>®</sup> Card?  </a>				
			<div class="expand-collapse--content">
				<p>Whether you're an Apple, Samsung, Android, or Microsoft user, mobile purchases are possible and offer you an easy way to pay using your card. Simply add your card to your device and get started.</p>
<p>All of the payment technologies use a form of encryption to create virtual card numbers (that is, your card's information isn't shared with a merchant).</p>
<p><a href="http://www.fidelityrewards.com/credit/digitalwallets.do" id="Link_1476975354652" name="Link_1476975354652">Learn more about making mobile payments</a></p>
<p><strong>Apple Pay<sup>®</sup></strong></p>
<p>Simply connect your card to enjoy the convenience of making payments with your Apple device and the safety and security of Apple Pay.</p>
<p><strong>Samsung Pay</strong></p>
<p>Use your phone's camera to add your card and secure it with a fingerprint and PIN number. Then, simply pay with an upward swipe on your screen.</p>
<p><strong>Android Pay<sup>TM</sup></strong></p>
<p>Once you've added your card to your device, simply hold it near the retailer's contactless terminal to pay. It’s also easy to make in-app payments.</p>
<p><strong>Microsoft Wallet</strong></p>
<p>Add your card to your Windows phone. Enter your device PIN and move your phone close to the contactless terminal to pay at your favorite store, coffee shop, or restaurant.</p> 
				
			</div> 
		</li> 
		
	 
		
		<li class="expand-collapse--question">
			<a href="#" class="expand-collapse--head expand-collapse--fancyexpand">Will my Elan card have chip technology?  </a>				
			<div class="expand-collapse--content">
				
        <p>Yes, it will have EMV chip functionality and security safeguards. A chip card is a standard-sized plastic credit card that contains an embedded microchip as well as the traditional magnetic stripe. When you buy something at a chip-enabled terminal, the chip encrypts the transaction information, preventing fraud and protecting your privacy.</p>
       
				
			</div> 
		</li> 
		
	 
		
		<li class="expand-collapse--question">
			<a href="#" class="expand-collapse--head expand-collapse--fancyexpand">What types of account alerts can I activate and receive?  </a>				
			<div class="expand-collapse--content">
				<p>Elan Cardmember Service offers notification alerts for the following situations:</p>
<ul>
<li>Online statement is available for viewing</li>
<li>Your balance exceeds an amount you specified</li>
<li>Due payment</li>
<li>Overdue payment</li>
<li>Payment posted to your account</li>
<li>Credits posted to your account</li>
<li>Debits posted to your account</li>
<li>A transaction has been authorized</li>
<li>A transaction has been authorized online or over the phone</li>
</ul> 
				
			</div> 
		</li> 
		
	 
		
		<li class="expand-collapse--question">
			<a href="#" class="expand-collapse--head expand-collapse--fancyexpand">What should I know about adding an authorized user to my account?  </a>				
			<div class="expand-collapse--content">
				<p>Your authorized user will have charging privileges. If you add an authorized user, you agree to be responsible for all charges they make on your account. If you want to <strong>remove</strong> an authorized user, please call <a href="javascript:void(0);" id="Link_1472589918012" name="Link_1472589918012" onclick="DisplayPopIn('tcm:526-249602', 'Link_1472589918012', '350', 'false')">Elan Cardmember Service</a>. Make sure you get the credit card back from the former user and destroy it.</p> 
				
			</div> 
		</li> 
		
	 
		
		<li class="expand-collapse--question">
			<a href="#" class="expand-collapse--head expand-collapse--fancyexpand">Can I change when my payments are due?  </a>				
			<div class="expand-collapse--content">
				<p>Yes, please call <a href="javascript:void(0);" id="Link_1472589979868" name="Link_1472589979868" onclick="DisplayPopIn('tcm:526-249602', 'Link_1472589979868', '350', 'false')">Elan Cardmember Service</a> to ask about changing your due date (statement date).</p> 
				
			</div> 
		</li> 
		
	 
		
		<li class="expand-collapse--question">
			<a href="#" class="expand-collapse--head expand-collapse--fancyexpand">How can I learn more about my new credit card?  </a>				
			<div class="expand-collapse--content">
				<p class="last-child">Please see <a href="/bin-public/060_www_fidelity_com/documents/fidelity/Visa-Learn-More-Non.pdf" id="Link_1472590104419" target="_blank" name="Link_1472590104419">Getting Started—Fidelity<sup>®</sup> Visa Signature<sup>®</sup> Credit Card (PDF)</a> for additional details.</p> 
				
			</div> 
		</li> 
		
	 
</ul>
